request.description:
This endpoint replaces an existing environment.

A sample body is added to the request that conforms to the following JSON schema:

```json
{
	"type": "object",
	"properties": {
		"environment": {
			"type": "object",
			"properties": {
				"name": {
					"type": "string",
					"maxLength": 254,
					"minLength": 1
				},
				"values": {
					"type": "array",
					"maxItems": 100,
					"additionalItems": false,
					"items": {
						"type": "object",
						"properties": {
							"key": {
								"type": "string",
								"maxLength": 254,
								"minLength": 1
							},
							"value": {
								"type": "string",
								"maxLength": 254,
								"minLength": 1
							},
							"type": {
								"type": "string"
							},
							"enabled": {
								"type": "boolean"
							}
						},
						"required": [
							"key",
							"value"
						]
					}
				}
			}
		}
	},
	"required": [
		"environment"
	]
}
```

On successful updation of the environment, the API returns the environment name and `id`.

> Requires <a href="#authentication">API Key</a> as `X-Api-Key` request header or `apikey` URL query parameter.

